# Fix Language Mixing in TTS Prompts

## Problem
Niche rules ([firearms.txt](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/prompts/tts_niche_rules/firearms.txt), [history.txt](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/prompts/tts_niche_rules/history.txt)) and [system_tts_verify.txt](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/prompts/system_tts_verify.txt) only have one version used for all languages. When `lang=es`, English pronunciation examples leak into Spanish context.

## Solution: Language-Aware Niche Rules

### Architecture Change

```
prompts/
  tts_niche_rules/
    firearms.txt          ← English (default)  
    history.txt           ← English (default)
    es/                   ← Spanish overrides
      firearms.txt        
      history.txt         
  es/
    system_tts_verify.txt ← NEW (Spanish verify examples)
```

### Code Change

#### [MODIFY] [load_niche_rules()](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/tts_cleanup.py#69-78) in [tts_cleanup.py](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/tts_cleanup.py)

Add [lang](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/rewrite_style_tab.py#392-394) parameter. Try `tts_niche_rules/{lang}/{niche}.txt` first, fallback to `tts_niche_rules/{niche}.txt`.

#### [MODIFY] [_run_cleanup()](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/tts_tab.py#496-814) in [tts_tab.py](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/tts_tab.py)

Pass [lang](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/rewrite_style_tab.py#392-394) to [load_niche_rules(niche, lang)](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/tts_cleanup.py#69-78).

